@node prefs "Prefs"

 These are programs that let you decide how TB4.0 works.

 @{" Help Prefs    " link hp}

 @{" Contents   " link main}
 
@endnode

@node hp "Help Prefs"

 This program lets you choose which program you want to view this guide
 with.  All TB programs can then read the config file and view this guide
 using the program you picked.

 To run the program double click on the HelpPrefs icon in the Prefs drawer.

 A window will apper with 4 Gadgets, 3 Button Gadgets and 1 String Gadget.

 @{fg shine}The String Gadget@{fg text} - next to the Find button lets you type in a program to
                     use.  The full path and name must be given eg
                     'SYS:Utilities/Multiview'.

 @{fg shine}The Find Button@{fg text} - makes the job of selecting a program easier.  When you
                   press this button a file requester will apper asking you
                   to select a program to use.  Press the Use button and the
                   program you selected will apper in the string gadget.
                   Press Cancel and the string gadget will not be affected.

 @{fg shine}The Save Button@{fg text} - Press this and the program you selected will be used by
                   TB4.0 to view this guide ( @{" Help " link 8} ).  This
                   will save the prefs to ENV: and ENVARC:

 @{fg shine}The Use Button@{fg text} - Press thts and the program you selected will be saved to
                  ENV: only.

 @{fg shine}The Cancel Button@{fg text} - Press this and the program used by TB4.0 will not
                     change.

 Note: That if you press Use it will only save the prefs to ram:env/  If you
       want to save the prefs forever use the Save button.  This saves the
       prefs to ram:env/ and envarc: - On your Workbench disk.

 @{" Contents " link main}

@endnode

