@node free "FreeWare"

 @{fg shine}What does FreeWare mean?@{fg text}

 In my oppion FreeWare means that the program/picture/animation/etc does not
 cost the user anything to use.  FreeWare is NOT PD.  Programs/pictures/etc
 that are classed as Public Domain (PD) have no copyright restrictions on
 them.  IE you can do what you want with them and the author can't do
 anything.

 FreeWare however, HAS GOT copyright restrictions on it.  These restrictions
 MUST be obeyed by the user, otherwise the user is breaking the law.

 @{fg shine}Please Note:-@{fg text} In basically the above defintion of FreeWare means that the
               of the copyright of the program remains the author's.

 @{fg shine}Basic Restrictions That FreeWare has:-@{fg text}

 @{fg shine}1@{fg text}. You may use the program as many times as you want and you do not
    have to pay anything unless you want to.

 @{fg shine}2@{fg text}. You may copy the program as many times as you want, as long as the
    archive or disk content is not altered.

 @{fg shine}3@{fg text}. You may NOT disassemble or change the program(s) in anyway without
    written permission from the author of the program(s).

 @{fg shine}4@{fg text}. If you use the program you accept these rules and the defintion of
    FreeWare written above.

 Other restictions may be added by authors.

 @{fg shine}NOTES:-@{fg text}

 @{fg shine}1@{fg text}. A seprate list of @{" Copyright " link 2} restrictions may be provided by
    the author's of FreeWare which may contain some points which are the
    same as those above.  @{" Copyright " link 2} restrictions must be read and obeyed.

 @{fg shine}2@{fg text}. Authors may also provide a @{" Disclaimer " link 2 24}.  This is basically says that
    if the computer is damaged in anyway while using the program, the author
    can NOT be held responsible for the damage caused.  IE you use the
    program at your own risk.

                                       
 @{" My Copyright " link 2}
